## File Map

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `frontend/src/hooks/useOracle.ts` | Fetches unified oracle/brief; returns sections or UNKNOWN |
| `frontend/src/components/killchain/AiBriefingPanel.tsx` | 3-tier routing: unified → backend KC → dev-only Groq |
| `frontend/src/components/killchain/types.ts` | `KillChainContext` type (snapshot schema) |
| `frontend/src/components/widgets/KillChainDashboard.tsx` | `buildContext()` — injects KC snapshot into every `setBrief` |
| `backend/app/api/v1/oracle.py` | Backend oracle proxy (Path 2 in routing above) |
| `frontend/.env.local` | `VITE_GROQ_API_KEY` dev-only key — never committed |
| `frontend/.env.production` | Must NOT contain `VITE_GROQ_API_KEY` |

---

## Context Passed to Oracle (KC Snapshot)

When Path 2 fires, the backend receives a typed `kill_chain_snapshot`:

```
score, verdict, direction, confluence, armed,
bullish_points, bearish_points, spy_spot,
triggered_count, total_checks, activations,
layers[]: { name, triggered, value, unit, signal }
```

Layer count is always derived from `layers.length` — no hardcoded "3/3" or "5/5" strings.

